<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06355188 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06355188 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Plans by the Israel Philharmonic to play works by German composer RichardWagner ran into a new hurdle Thursday when an advisory committee decided topoll subscribers on the issue. The orchestra raised an outcry when it decidedFriday to break a 53-year-old ban on scheduled performances by the Germancomposer. Wagner died before the Nazis came to power in Germany, but AdolfHitler admired his anti-Semitic writings and ordered Wagner played at Naziparty functions.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  General News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  NEW ISRAELI HURDLE FOR WAGNER MUSIC  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Foreign News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911220  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  83  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, December 20, 199100355188,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>